<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Uman</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><b>Solution to the DoT problem:</b><br />
<br />
Absor says (and I agree) that DoTs are underpowered, especially in groups.  He says (and I agree somewhat) that the Affliction focus effects are too good to be applied to spells like charm, slow, or root.<br />
<br />
Here is the fix:<br />
<br />
tell a programmer to systematically increase the duration, decrease mana cost, and decrease casting time of all DoT spells by 10%, making sure that 6 tick spells actually go to 7 ticks - something which doesn't happen reliably with the focus effect =(<br />
<br />
Now, change the "Affliction" focus effect back to how it was the last 9 months (remove the "hitpoints allowed" restriction), except decrease the effects to 18% haste, mana saving, and duration.  These are effects that high end players can get (Solusek focus) so it would not present any game balance issues.  If charm is intended to be excluded, that can be done easily enough (I do not think it should be)<br />
<br />
This is the only solution that satisfies the SoE's stated (and legitimate) game design aims while <b>not screwing and enraging the affected customers to the point of leaving the game</b>.  That's right, we're customers.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=5d19667afc90a94c382e87e4499a87af&amp;postid=118593">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=5d19667afc90a94c382e87e4499a87af&amp;do=getip&postid=118593">Logged</a></div>
	
	<!-- / message -->
		
	</td>
